<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1841,1938]" pageId="9" pageNumber="242">
Described on the basis of a single specimen from Baltic amber (
<bibRefCitation author="Polilov" box="[873,1180,1841,1866]" pageId="9" pageNumber="242" refString="Polilov, A. A. &amp; Perkovsky, E. E. (2004) New species of Late Eocene feather - winged beetles (Coleoptera, Ptiliidae) from the Rovno and Baltic Amber [in Russian]. Paleontologicheskii Zhurnal, 2004 (6), 73 - 77. [English translation in Paleontological Journal, 38, (6), 664 - 668]" type="journal article" year="2004">Polilov &amp; Perkovsky 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The photographs and line drawings included in the paper do not show the mesoventral carinae defining the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1293,1877,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiliidae" genus="Micridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1293,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="242">Micridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described here and the two depressions on the pronotum are rounded and not linear.
</paragraph>
